postcontent: This handgun retains about 55% of its metal finish. There is very light pinprick surface erosion scattered over the left side of the slide from the muzzle back about 2”. There is surface loss at the front underside of the slide and on the edges of the slide and frame and thinning in the remainder of the surfaces. There are a few tiny nicks in the bottom edges of the slide, and multiple tiny dings scattered over the sides and underside of the slide, with light handling marks scattered over the frame. The safety checkering shows moderate wear and the slide release checkering is sharp to the touch. The screw heads are sharp except for the upper screw on the right side, which is distressed. The markings are clear except for the proof mark on the barrel, which was lightly struck. Overall, this handgun rates in about Good to Very Good condition.

These are for the advanced collector.Late war Winchester $1600Late War Inland $1500The winchester has the type III barrel band and the Inland has a type II.Both have round bolts and adjustable sights.These are not mixmasters.
